graded_questions.question:
Consider the following C++ code snippet:
```cpp
int x = 10;
if (x > 10) {
    std::cout << "Greater";
} else if (x == 10) {
    std::cout << "Equal";
} else {
    std::cout << "Smaller";
}
```
What will be the output when this code is executed?

How many times will the word "Loop" be printed by the following `for` loop in C++?
```cpp
for (int i = 1; i <= 3; i++) {
    std::cout << "Loop";
}
```

